tHub PRs, the pull request number should map to the `but-agentlog`\n   113\t`review` target. For example, PR `13936` should query the review target value\n   114\t`13936`, which `but-agentlog` normalizes to the stored key:\n   115\t\n   116\t```text\n   117\tgitbutler-review:13936\n   118\t```\n   119\t\n   120\tThis review target is optional because captured metadata may not always include\n   121\treview information. When it is present, it is the st\n[TRUNCATED]\n46\ttreating branch-only matches as proof that the session belongs to the PR.\n   147\t\n   148\tChange target lookup is not relevant for the MVP. It can be considered later if\n   149\tAgent Trail needs a deeper GitButler-specific view of stacked changes.\n   150\t\n   151\tAccess can come from:\n   152\t\n   153\t- the repository being public/open source\n   154\t- the user authenticating with GitHub\n   155\t- a GitButler or Forge installation having repository access\n   156\t- a previously published trail snapshot with an allowed share policy\n   157\t\n   158\tThe first version should focus on public/open-source repositories. Private\n   159\trepository access, GitHub OAuth, GitButler workspace access, and explicit share\n   160\tlinks can come later.\n   161\t\n   162\tThis entry point should still respect the publication boundary. Rewriting a URL\n   163\tshould not automatically expose private captured context. It should create a\n   164\trequest for an Agent Trail, then show one of:\n   165\t\n   166\t- an existing published trail\n   167\t- a newly generated review-safe overview, if access and policy allow it\n   168\t- an authentication prompt\n   169\t- a clear \"no trail available\" state\n   170\t\n   171\tOn-demand generation is attractive because it avoids needing every PR to be\n   172\tpre-linked by GitButler. It also gives reviewers a memorable gesture: replace\n   173\tthe forge domain with the Agent Trail domain.\n   174\t\n   175\tOpen design questions:\n   176\t\n   177\t- Should generated trails be cached automatically?\n   178\t- Who can publish or persist the generated result?\n   179\t- What should happen when no captured agentlog data exists for the PR?\n   180\t- How should GitHub authentication map to GitMeta/Forge access?\n   181\t\n   182\t## Data Source\n   183\t\n   184\tAgent Trail should build on `but-agentlog` primitives:\n   185\t\n   186\t- durable project-scoped agent sessions\n   187\t- capture turns inside sessions\n   188\t- transcript records inside turns\n   189\t- observed branch, review, and change targets\n   190\t- verified related-session lookup\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T14:42:00.374Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}